{"markdown":{"yaml":{"format":"html"},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"linux-page\">\n\n  <div class=\"wd-hero content-section\" style=\"padding-top: 4rem; padding-bottom: 2rem;\">\n\n    <div class=\"wd-hero-copy\">\n      \n      <div class=\"wd-hero-title\">\n        Master<br>\n        <span class=\"accent\">Linux</span> &amp;<br>\n        <span class=\"rhel\">RHEL</span>\n      </div>\n      \n      <p class=\"wd-hero-subtitle\">\n        From your first terminal command to managing production-grade \n        Red Hat servers — a curriculum built for sysadmins who mean business.\n      </p>\n\n      \n\n      <div class=\"terminal-prompt\">\n        <span class=\"prompt-user\">admin</span><span class=\"prompt-at\">@</span><span class=\"prompt-host\">akademiyaa</span>\n        <span class=\"prompt-path\">~/career $</span>\n        <span class=\"prompt-cmd\">enroll --course linux</span>\n        <span class=\"cursor\"></span>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"wd-hero-actions\">\n        <a href=\"/contact.qmd\" class=\"btn-primary-wd\">Start Learning</a>\n        <a href=\"#modules\" class=\"btn-ghost-wd\">View Curriculum ↓</a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"wd-hero-visual\">\n      <div class=\"linux-stats-grid\">\n        <div class=\"linux-stat-card\">\n          <span class=\"linux-stat-num\">4</span>\n          <span class=\"linux-stat-label\">Core Modules</span>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"linux-stat-card\">\n          <span class=\"linux-stat-num\">RHCSA</span>\n          <span class=\"linux-stat-label\">Cert Aligned</span>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"linux-stat-card\">\n          <span class=\"linux-stat-num\">∞</span>\n          <span class=\"linux-stat-label\">Lab Access</span>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n  \n  <section class=\"content-section\" style=\"padding-top: 1rem; padding-bottom: 2rem;\">\n    <div class=\"linux-benefits-grid\">\n      \n      <div class=\"benefit-card\">\n        <div class=\"benefit-icon\">🎥</div> \n        <h4>Lifetime Recordings</h4>\n        <p>Revisit any class session, anytime. Your video access never expires.</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"benefit-card\">\n        <div class=\"benefit-icon\">📝</div>\n        <h4>Premium Notes</h4>\n        <p>Get exclusive downloadable study materials, commands, and guides.</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"benefit-card\">\n        <div class=\"benefit-icon\">🤝</div>\n        <h4>Lifetime Mentorship</h4>\n        <p>Get direct career guidance and support long after you finish the course.</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"benefit-card\">\n        <div class=\"benefit-icon\">💼</div>\n        <h4>Premium Job Portal</h4>\n        <p>Gain exclusive access to our hiring network for rapid career growth.</p>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"tools-strip content-section\" style=\"margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 2rem; padding-bottom: 4rem;\">\n    <div style=\"text-align: center;\">\n      <div class=\"tools-label\">Technologies &amp; Tools Covered</div>\n      <div class=\"tools-row\">\n        <span class=\"tool-box\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>RHEL 9</span>\n        <span class=\"tool-box\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>systemd</span>\n        <span class=\"tool-box\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>dnf / rpm</span>\n        <span class=\"tool-box\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>SELinux</span>\n        <span class=\"tool-box\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>firewalld</span>\n        <span class=\"tool-box\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>LVM</span>\n        <span class=\"tool-box\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>Bash Scripting</span>\n        <span class=\"tool-box\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>SSH / OpenSSH</span>\n        <span class=\"tool-box\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>Cron / at</span>\n        <span class=\"tool-box\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>NFS / Samba</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n    \n<section id=\"modules\" class=\"content-section\" style=\"padding-top: 0;\">\n    \n    <div style=\"max-width: 850px; margin-bottom: 3rem;\">\n      <div class=\"section-label\">Curriculum</div>\n      <h2 class=\"section-title\">Four Core Modules</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-body\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\">\n        Each module builds on the last — from foundational CLI fluency to \n        automated, production-hardened server management.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"linux-modules-grid\">\n\n      <div class=\"linux-mod-card mod-1\" data-num=\"01\">\n        <div class=\"mod-header\">\n          <div class=\"mod-icon\">🐧</div>\n          <h3 class=\"mod-title\">Linux Fundamentals</h3>\n        </div>\n        <p class=\"mod-desc\">Build unshakeable foundations. Navigate the filesystem hierarchy, master permissions and ownership, and get comfortable with the terminal before diving deeper.</p>\n        \n        <div class=\"mod-topics-expand\">\n          <div class=\"mod-topics-inner\">\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">CLI navigation</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">chmod / chown</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">Filesystem Hierarchy</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">Processes &amp; Signals</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">vim / nano</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">Pipelines</span>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"linux-mod-card mod-2\" data-num=\"02\">\n        <div class=\"mod-header\">\n          <div class=\"mod-icon\">🔴</div>\n          <h3 class=\"mod-title\">RHEL Administration</h3>\n        </div>\n        <p class=\"mod-desc\">Go deep on RHEL 9. Master package management, user and group administration, systemd service control, and storage provisioning with LVM.</p>\n        \n        <div class=\"mod-topics-expand\">\n          <div class=\"mod-topics-inner\">\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">dnf / rpm</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">useradd / groupmod</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">systemctl</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">LVM &amp; Partitioning</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">journalctl</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">grub2</span>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"linux-mod-card mod-3\" data-num=\"03\">\n        <div class=\"mod-header\">\n          <div class=\"mod-icon\">🛡️</div>\n          <h3 class=\"mod-title\">Security &amp; Networking</h3>\n        </div>\n        <p class=\"mod-desc\">Lock down your servers. Configure firewalld zones, write and audit SELinux policies, and establish hardened SSH access for safe remote administration.</p>\n        \n        <div class=\"mod-topics-expand\">\n          <div class=\"mod-topics-inner\">\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">firewalld</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">SELinux policies</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">SSH hardening</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">PAM</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">auditd</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">fail2ban</span>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"linux-mod-card mod-4\" data-num=\"04\">\n        <div class=\"mod-header\">\n          <div class=\"mod-icon\">⚙️</div>\n          <h3 class=\"mod-title\">Automation &amp; Scripting</h3>\n        </div>\n        <p class=\"mod-desc\">Stop clicking and start scripting. Write robust Bash scripts to automate routine admin tasks, handle errors gracefully, and deploy servers with speed.</p>\n        \n        <div class=\"mod-topics-expand\">\n          <div class=\"mod-topics-inner\">\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">Bash scripting</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">cron &amp; at</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">Functions &amp; Arrays</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">Error handling</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">Heredocs</span>\n            <span class=\"mod-topic\">Logging</span>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n  </section>\n  \n  <section class=\"content-section\" style=\"padding-top: 4rem;\">\n    <div style=\"max-width: 600px; margin-bottom: 4rem;\">\n      <div class=\"section-label\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem;\">Learning Path</div>\n      <h2 class=\"section-title\">Your Roadmap to RHCSA</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-body\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\">\n        A structured, no-fluff progression from zero to certified Red Hat System Administrator.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"rhcsa-timeline\">\n\n      <div class=\"rhcsa-step\">\n        <div class=\"rhcsa-dot\"></div>\n        <div class=\"rhcsa-content\">\n          <h4>Set Up Your Lab Environment</h4>\n          <p>Install RHEL 9 in a VM or spin up a cloud instance. Learn how to access the terminal, configure a static IP, and navigate your first shell session.</p>\n          <span class=\"rhcsa-duration\">⏱ Week 1</span>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"rhcsa-step\">\n        <div class=\"rhcsa-dot\"></div>\n        <div class=\"rhcsa-content\">\n          <h4>CLI Fluency &amp; Filesystem Mastery</h4>\n          <p>Get comfortable with file operations, searching, redirection, and permissions. Practice with real-world scenarios, not contrived exercises.</p>\n          <span class=\"rhcsa-duration\">⏱ Weeks 2–3</span>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"rhcsa-step\">\n        <div class=\"rhcsa-dot\"></div>\n        <div class=\"rhcsa-content\">\n          <h4>RHEL Administration Deep-Dive</h4>\n          <p>Manage packages, users, services, and storage. Configure a multi-disk LVM layout and understand how RHEL boots and recovers.</p>\n          <span class=\"rhcsa-duration\">⏱ Weeks 4–6</span>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"rhcsa-step\">\n        <div class=\"rhcsa-dot\"></div>\n        <div class=\"rhcsa-content\"